Here's a detailed scenario: 

Imagine a Smart Factory where multiple machines (agents) work together to optimize production and reduce energy consumption. There are three types of agents:
1. ProductionAgent: Controls manufacturing equipment and optimizes production processes.
2. EnergyAgent: Monitors and optimizes energy consumption.
3. MaintenanceAgent: Predicts and schedules maintenance activities.

These agents work together to optimize the overall production process. They exchange relevant information, negotiate, and coordinate actions dynamically, adapting to changing conditions.

To demonstrate their communication and collaboration, we'll write a simple C# code using gRPC.

1. Install gRPC NuGet packages in your C# project:
- Grpc.AspNetCore
- Grpc.Tools
- Google.Protobuf

2. Define the gRPC service file (.proto file) describing the communication protocol for agents:
```
syntax = "proto3";

package Agent;

service AgentCommunication {
  rpc ShareInformation (InformationRequest) returns (InformationReply);
}

message InformationRequest {
  string sender = 1;
  string infoType = 2;
  string data = 3;
}

message InformationReply {
  string receiver = 1;
  bool status = 2;
}
```

3. Implement the gRPC service for each agent type (e.g., ProductionAgent):
```csharp
using Agent;
using Grpc.Core;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

public class ProductionAgentService : AgentCommunication.AgentCommunicationBase
{
    public override Task<InformationReply> ShareInformation(InformationRequest request, ServerCallContext context)
    {
        // Process received information
        string infoType = request.InfoType;
        string data = request.Data;
        // ...

        // Send a response indicating whether the information was processed successfully
        return Task.FromResult(new InformationReply { Receiver = "ProductionAgent", Status = true });
    }
}
```

4. Implement the gRPC client for agent communication:
```csharp
using Agent;
using Grpc.Core;
using System;

public class AgentClient
{
    private readonly AgentCommunication.AgentCommunicationClient _client;

    public AgentClient(AgentCommunication.AgentCommunicationClient client)
    {
        _client = client;
    }

    public void ShareInformation(string sender, string infoType, string data)
    {
        var request = new InformationRequest { Sender = sender, InfoType = infoType, Data = data };
        try
        {
            var response = _client.ShareInformation(request);
            Console.WriteLine($"Information sent by {sender}: {infoType}, {data}.");
        }
        catch (Exception ex)
        {
            Console.WriteLine($"Error sending information: {ex.Message}");
        }
    }
}
```

5. Set up the agents to communicate with each other using the gRPC client.

