Assuming that you already have a working PHP code to randomly select 10 words expressing sadness from the JSON data, here's how you can modify the code to exclude synonyms:

```php
<?php
$url = "YOUR_SYNONYM_API_URL_HERE"; // Replace with the API URL for synonyms
$sad_words_json = file_get_contents("sad_words.json");
$sad_words = json_decode($sad_words_json, true);

function getSynonyms($word, $url) {
    $api_url = str_replace("{{word}}", $word, $url); // Replace {{word}} with the actual word in the URL
    $synonyms_json = file_get_contents($api_url);
    if ($synonyms_json === false) {
        return [];
    }
    $synonyms_data = json_decode($synonyms_json, true);
    $synonyms = [];
    // The response structure depends on your specific API, here get the synonyms property
    if (isset($synonyms_data['synonyms'])) {
        $synonyms = $synonyms_data['synonyms'];
    }
    return $synonyms;
}

function getRandomWords($words, $count, $url) {
    $unique_words = [];
    $excluded_words = [];

    while (count($unique_words) < $count) {
        $random_word = $words[array_rand($words)];

        if (in_array($random_word, $excluded_words)) {
            continue;
        }

        $synonyms = getSynonyms($random_word, $url);
        $excluded_words = array_merge($excluded_words, $synonyms);
        $unique_words[] = $random_word;
    }

    return $unique_words;
}

$unique_sad_words = getRandomWords($sad_words, 10, $url);
echo json_encode($unique_sad_words);
?>
```

Remember to replace `"YOUR_SYNONYM_API_URL_HERE"` with the actual API endpoint for the synonyms, and use the API's response structure to extract the synonyms.

This code will make API requests to get synonyms and then exclude them from the list while selecting 10 unique words. Don't forget, you will need an API key or access token if the synonyms API requires it. Make sure to consult the API documentation for setup and usage instructions.

