    <div id="display"></div>

    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

In the above HTML, a text input and a button are created. When the button is clicked, the 'getMovieInfo' function is called. This function sends a GET request to the OMDB API.

Next, create a 'script.js' file and add the following code:

```javascript
function getMovieInfo() {
    var movieTitle = $("#movie").val().trim();

    if (movieTitle !== "") {
        var url = "http://www.omdbapi.com/?t=" + movieTitle + "&apikey=YOUR_API_KEY";

        $.getJSON(url, function(data) {
            var movieDisplay = "<h2>" + data.Title + "</h2>" +
                               "<h3>Setting: " + data.Set.name + "</h3>" +
                               "<h3>Main Characters:</h3>" +
                               "<ul>";

            $.each(data.Actors, function(index, actor) {
                movieDisplay += "<li>" + actor + "</li>";
            });

            movieDisplay += "</ul>";

            $("#display").html(movieDisplay);
        });
    } else {
        alert("Please enter a movie title.");
    }
}
```

This JavaScript code is attached to the 'getMovieInfo' function. When the function is called, it retrieves the movie title from the input field, trims it, and then constructs an API call to the OMDB API. It then parses the JSON response into a JavaScript object and extracts the movie title, setting, and main characters. This information is then displayed in the 'display' div on the webpage.

Please replace 'YOUR_API_KEY' in the url with your actual API key from OMDB.

