To modify a PHP function to analyze the tone of a given text using IBM Watson's Tone Analyzer API and return data in XML format, follow the steps below:

1. Sign up for an IBM Cloud account to get API access if you don't have one: [IBM Cloud](https://cloud.ibm.com/)

2. Create an instance of Tone Analyzer API. Go to [Tone Analyzer API](https://cloud.ibm.com/catalog/services/tone-analyzer) and click on `Create`. Once the instance is created, open it, and copy the API Key and URL.

3. Install the "ibm-watson" SDK in your project:

```sh
composer require ibm-watson/sdk
```

4. Modify the PHP function:

```php
<?php
// Include the required dependencies
require 'vendor/autoload.php';
use IBM\Watson\ToneAnalyzer\ToneAnalyzer;
use IBM\Watson\ToneAnalyzer\Model\ToneAnalysis;
use GuzzleHttp\Exception\GuzzleException;

function analyzeTone($text) {
    // Replace these variables with your own API credentials
    $apiKey = 'YOUR_API_KEY';
    $url = 'YOUR_API_URL';

    // Create a new ToneAnalyzer instance
    $toneAnalyzer = new ToneAnalyzer(v4, [
        'apiKey' => $apiKey,
    ]);

    $toneAnalyzer->setServiceUrl($url);

    try {
        // Analyze the tone using the Tone Analyzer API
        $result = $toneAnalyzer->tone([
            'tone_input' => ['text' => $text],
            'content_type' => 'application/json',
        ]);

        // Convert the result to XML format
        $xml_data = new SimpleXMLElement('<?xml version="1.0"?><data></data>');
        array_to_xml((array)$result->getResult(), $xml_data);

        // Return the XML data
        return $xml_data->asXML();
    } catch (GuzzleException $e) {
        // Handle any exceptions that may occur
        return 'Error: ' . $e->getMessage();
    }
}

function array_to_xml($data, &$xml_data) {
    foreach ($data as $key => $value) {
        if (is_numeric($key)) {
            $key = 'item' . $key;
        }
        if (is_array($value)) {
            $subnode = $xml_data->addChild($key);
            array_to_xml($value, $subnode);
        } else {
            $xml_data->addChild($key, htmlspecialchars($value));
        }
    }
}
?>
```

Make sure to replace 'YOUR_API_KEY' and 'YOUR_API_URL' with your actual Tone Analyzer API key and URL.

Here's an example of how to use the `analyzeTone` function:

```php
$text = "I am very happy today, the weather is great!";
$xmlData = analyzeTone($text);
header('Content-Type: text/xml');
echo $xmlData;
```

This modified function will analyze the tone of the input text, categorize it based on emotions, social tendencies, and language styles using IBM Watson Tone Analyzer API, and return the data in properly formatted XML format. The `array_to_xml` function is used to convert the associative array into XML format with appropriate tags and attributes, making it easier to parse and manipulate.

