For Java programs, you'll primarily be using Java libraries and frameworks, while web applications typically involve JavaScript and its libraries. In this case, we'll discuss the implementation of voice recognition using the Google Cloud Speech-to-Text API in a Java program.

To create a Java program that utilizes the Google Cloud Speech-to-Text API for real-time transcription from a microphone input, follow the steps below:

**Step 1: Set up the Google Cloud Speech-to-Text API**
1. Create a new project in the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/).
2. Enable the [Speech-to-Text API](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/speech.googleapis.com) for your project.
3. Create an API key for your project in the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials).

**Step 2: Install the Google Cloud Client Library for Java**
1. Add the Google Cloud Speech API to your project's dependencies. Modify your project's build.gradle or pom.xml file:
   * For Gradle:
     ```
     implementation 'com.google.cloud:google-cloud-speech:2.1.0'
     ```
   * For Maven:
     ```
     <dependency>
       <groupId>com.google.cloud</groupId>
       <artifactId>google-cloud-speech</artifactId>
       <version>2.1.0</version>
     </dependency>
     ```

**Step 3: Set up authentication**
1. Create a JSON key file for Google Cloud credentials. In the [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials), click on “Create Credentials” and choose "Service Account Key".
2. Assign a "Project > Owner" role.
3. Store the JSON key file securely and create an environment variable referencing it:
   ```
   export GOOGLE_APPLICATION_CREDENTIALS="/path/to/your/keyfile.json"
   ```

**Step 4: Create a Java program**
1. Create a new Java file and import the necessary dependencies:

   ```java
   import com.google.api.gax.rpc.ApiStreamObserver;
   import com.google.api.gax.rpc.BidiStreamingCallable;
   import com.google.api.gax.rpc.ClientStream;
   import com.google.cloud.speech.v1.*;
   import org.apache.log4j.BasicConfigurator;
   import javax.sound.sampled.*;
   import java.io.IOException;
   import java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue;
   import java.util.concurrent.LinkedBlockingDeque;
   ```

2. Create a MicrophoneStreamingRecognize class to handle microphone input and communicate with the Google Cloud Speech-to-Text API.

   ```java
   public class MicrophoneStreamingRecognize {
       private static final int SAMPLE_RATE = 16000;
       private static final int SAMPLE_SIZE_IN_BITS = 16;
       private static final int CHANNELS = 1;
       private static final boolean SIGNED = true;
       private static final boolean BIG_ENDIAN = false;
       private static final AudioFormat FORMAT = new AudioFormat(SAMPLE_RATE, SAMPLE_SIZE_IN_BITS, CHANNELS, SIGNED, BIG_ENDIAN);
       private static final DataLine.Info INFO = new DataLine.Info(TargetDataLine.class, FORMAT);

       private final BlockingQueue<byte[]> sharedQueue = new LinkedBlockingDeque<>();
       private volatile boolean done = false;

       private void run() throws Exception {
           BasicConfigurator.configure();

           try (SpeechClient client = SpeechClient.create()) {

               BidiStreamingCallable<StreamingRecognizeRequest, StreamingRecognizeResponse> callable =
                       client.streamingRecognizeCallable();

               ResponseApiStreamingObserver<StreamingRecognizeResponse> responseObserver =
                       new ResponseApiStreamingObserver<>();

               try (ClientStream<StreamingRecognizeRequest> requestObserver =
                            callable.bidiStreamingCall(responseObserver)) {

                   // Prepare audio request with the microphone input
                   StreamingRecognizeRequest.newBuilder()
                           .setStreamingConfig(
                                   StreamingRecognitionConfig.newBuilder()
                                           .setConfig(
                                                   RecognitionConfig.newBuilder()
                                                           .setEncoding(RecognitionConfig.AudioEncoding.LINEAR16)
                                                           .setLanguageCode("en-US")
                                                           .setSampleRateHertz(SAMPLE_RATE)
                                                           .build())
                                           .setInterimResults(true)
                                           .build())
                           .build();

                   // Start streaming microphone input
                   startMicrophone(requestObserver);

                   // Read and process the transcription responses from the API
                   while (!done) {
                       StreamingRecognizeResponse response = responseObserver.takeResponse();
                       response.getResultsList().stream()
                               .map(StreamingRecognitionResult::getAlternativesList)
                               .forEach(alternatives -> alternatives.forEach(alternative ->
                                       System.out.println("Transcript: " + alternative.getTranscript())));
                   }
               }
           }
       }

